<paragraph blockId="73.[264,1322,1479,1705]" box="[264,382,1479,1504]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis box="[264,382,1479,1504]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="73.[264,1322,1479,1705]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Larva: anterior cephalic apotome markedly pale anteriorly, head spot pattern in Eiffel Tower configuration; posterior edge of cephalic apotome markedly emarginated, postocciput extended between cervical sclerites and apotome, hypostomal teeth not markedly developed; abdomen moderately steatopygous, posterior circlet directed posteriorly; dorsal tubercles absent.</paragraph>
